{meta: title In The Shadows Of The Wine}
{meta: artist Porter Wagoner}
{meta: composer Dusty Rose}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]In the shadows of the wine
[F]I see your face before me all the [C]time
[F]And there you're smiling from this glass of [C]mine
[G7]In the shadows of the [C]wine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]I'd lift the glass and there you're [C]standing
[F]The love I won and lost no longer [C]mine
[F]I see the past unfold before [C]me
[G7]In the shadows of the [C]wine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Wilder music stronger wine
[F]Though I'm unhappy dear the wine is [C]kind
[F]I see you dancing in this glass of [C]mine
[G7]Play more music drink more [C]wine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]When midnight comes I'll feel no [C]sorrow
[F]And from the glass you'll smile and wave [C]goodbye
[F]But we will meet again [C]tomorrow
[G7]In the shadows of the [C]wine
{end_of_verse}
